To Get started
Simple Typescript Project creation
1. Run npm init -y to create package.json
2. use the [npm i --save-dev typescript] or [npm install typescript --save-dev] (To install typescript)
3. To run the compiler use npx tsc
4. To create the config file use npx tsc --init (To create the tsconfig.json file)
5. under script in the package.json change the test to another name and add tsc to it example(runDev:"tsc")
    This will compile the code everytime you call the variable name runDev example (npm run runDev)
6. Create an index.ts, when compiled will create a index.js.



Creating Project with a Package called Vite 
1. npm init vite@latest add-project-name-here -- --template vanilla-ts example (npm init vite@latest web-porfolio -- --template vanilla-ts)
2. Then npm install (It generates our node modules) 
3. Then npm run dev (It creates our url)
4. We can also do npm run build  






From W3School
6. Add the following to the tsconfig file 
{
  "include": ["src"],
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./build"
  }
}
7. Create your src folder. This is where you will store your typescript files
8. Create your index.ts file in the src folder
